  "text": "The event handler chain from API server watch events to informer cache updates in Kubernetes follows this flow:\n\n1. **Watch Initiation (ListWatch)**: The ListWatch type (tools/cache/listwatch.go) provides List() and Watch() methods that connect to the API server. The Watch() method returns a watch.Interface that streams events from the API server.\n\n2. **Reflector (tools/cache/reflector.go)**: The Reflector type drives the entire flow. Its Run() method starts an infinite loop calling ListAndWatch(). The ListAndWatch() method first lists all objects, then calls watch() to set up a continuous watch stream. The watch() method calls handleWatch()/handleAnyWatch() to process events.\n\n3. **Processing Watch Events (reflector.go)**: handleAnyWatch() receives events from the API server via w.ResultChan() and processes them as watch.Added, watch.Modified, or watch.Deleted events. These events are immediately added to the store via store.Add(), store.Update(), or store.Delete().\n\n4. **DeltaFIFO Queue (tools/cache/delta_fifo.go)**: The store backing the Reflector is a DeltaFIFO - a queue that accumulates change deltas. Each call to Add/Update/Delete creates or appends to a Deltas object for that key. This FIFO stores deltas indexed by object key, allowing processing of all changes for an object together.\n\n5. **Controller Loop (tools/cache/controller.go)**: A Controller runs a loop that pops Deltas objects from the DeltaFIFO queue. Each pop call returns accumulated Deltas for a single object. The controller invokes the ProcessFunc for each popped item.\n\n6. **ProcessFunc and processDeltas (controller.go)**: The ProcessFunc is called with the Deltas object and delegates to processDeltas(). This function iterates through each Delta, updates the local cache (clientState), and calls the appropriate handler method (handler.OnAdd, handler.OnUpdate, or handler.OnDelete).\n\n7. **SharedIndexInformer (tools/cache/shared_informer.go)**: The sharedIndexInformer type implements the ResourceEventHandler interface. Its OnAdd(), OnUpdate(), and OnDelete() methods receive notifications from processDeltas(). These methods update the local index cache and immediately delegate to the sharedProcessor.distribute() method.\n\n8. **SharedProcessor (shared_informer.go)**: The sharedProcessor maintains a map of all registered processorListeners. Its distribute() method iterates through all listeners and calls listener.add() to queue the notification, considering whether it's a sync event or normal event.\n\n9. **ProcessorListener (shared_informer.go)**: Each registered ResourceEventHandler gets its own processorListener. The listener has two goroutines: pop() which transfers notifications from an unbounded ring buffer to a channel, and run() which reads from that channel and invokes the actual handler methods.\n\n10. **Handler Invocation (shared_informer.go)**: The processorListener.run() method reads notifications from nextCh and invokes the appropriate handler method based on notification type. For addNotification, it calls handler.OnAdd(). For updateNotification, handler.OnUpdate(). For deleteNotification, handler.OnDelete().\n\nThis architecture achieves several goals: (1) Multiple event handlers can register with a single informer via AddEventHandler(); (2) Events are buffered through the DeltaFIFO to handle back-pressure and accumulate changes; (3) Each handler runs in its own goroutine with its own buffer, preventing slow handlers from blocking others; (4) Events are guaranteed to be processed in order for each object; (5) Resync events can trigger re-listing all objects periodically.\n\nThe complete files involved are:\n- ListWatch implementation: tools/cache/listwatch.go\n- Watch event processing: tools/cache/reflector.go (handleAnyWatch, watch methods)\n- Delta accumulation: tools/cache/delta_fifo.go (DeltaFIFO type)\n- Event processing loop: tools/cache/controller.go (processDeltas function)\n- Event distribution to handlers: tools/cache/shared_informer.go (sharedIndexInformer, sharedProcessor, processorListener)\n- Store interface: tools/cache/store.go"
}

